==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Predict
<hw>Pre*dict"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Predicted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Predicting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>praedictus</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>praedicere</ets> to predict; <ets>prae</ets> before +
<ets>dicere</ets> to say, tell. See <er>Diction</er>, and cf.
<er>Preach</er>.]</ety> <def>To tell or declare beforehand; to foretell;
to prophesy; to presage; <as>as, to <ex>predict</ex> misfortune; to
<ex>predict</ex> the return of a comet.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To foretell; prophesy; prognosticate; presage;
forebode; foreshow; bode.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predict</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Predict
<hw>Pre*dict"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A prediction.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predictable</ent>⟦br⟧
